        "translation": "Huilang said.",
        "source": "T37n1763_014:0435c25_1",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "迦葉因釋解脫。",
        "translation": "\"Kāśyapa's explanation of liberation is based on this phrase.",
        "source": "T37n1763_014:0435c25_2",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "有此句也。",
        "translation": "It has this phrase.",
        "source": "T37n1763_014:0435c25_3",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "故以為難。",
        "translation": "That's why it's considered difficult.",
        "source": "T37n1763_014:0435c25_4",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "請重釋也。",
        "translation": "Please re-explain it.",
        "source": "T37n1763_014:0435c26_5",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "佛告迦葉善男子是事不然(至)不可以譬烏鵲之音。",
        "translation": "The Buddha told Kāśyapa, \"Good sons, this is not the case.\" (Until) It can't be likened to the sound of a crow magpie.",
        "source": "T37n1763_014:0435c27_0",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "案。",
        "translation": "Commentary.",
        "source": "T37n1763_014:0435c28_1",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "僧亮曰。",
        "translation": "Sengliang said.",
        "source": "T37n1763_014:0435c28_2",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "以鳥譬鳥。",
        "translation": "\"A bird is an analogy for a bird.",
        "source": "T37n1763_014:0435c28_3",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "以聲譬聲。",
        "translation": "He uses sound to simulate sound.",
        "source": "T37n1763_014:0435c28_4",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "遍取同鳥。",
        "translation": "It's generally taken to be the same as a bird.",
        "source": "T37n1763_014:0435c28_5",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "不得相比也。",
        "translation": "It can't be compared with it.",
        "source": "T37n1763_014:0435c29_6",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "分取可譬佛聲也。",
        "translation": "Taking it separately can be likened to the Buddha's voice.",
        "source": "T37n1763_014:0435c29_7",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "爾時佛讚迦葉善哉善哉(至)知諸法性皆亦如是。",
        "translation": "It was then that the Buddha praised Kāśyapa, \"Good, good!\" (to know that the nature of all dharmas is likewise).",
        "source": "T37n1763_014:0436a01_0",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "案。",
        "translation": "Commentary.",
        "source": "T37n1763_014:0436a02_1",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "僧亮曰。",
        "translation": "Sengliang said.",
        "source": "T37n1763_014:0436a02_2",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "以是因緣者。",
        "translation": "'By these causes and conditions,' he said.",
        "source": "T37n1763_014:0436a02_3",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "少分因緣也。",
        "translation": "It's a small set of causes and conditions.",
        "source": "T37n1763_014:0436a02_4",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "無能匹者。",
        "translation": "There's no match for it.",
        "source": "T37n1763_014:0436a02_5",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "非遍喻也。",
        "translation": "It's not a universal metaphor.",
        "source": "T37n1763_014:0436a03_6",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "為喻者少分也。",
        "translation": "It's a metaphor for a small part.",
        "source": "T37n1763_014:0436a03_7",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "迦葉復言云何如來(至)成就滿故名大般涅槃。",
        "translation": "Kāśyapa also said, \"How did the Tathāgata (come) accomplish the full accomplishment and therefore be called great extinction?",
        "source": "T37n1763_014:0436a04_0",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "案。",
        "translation": "Commentary.",
        "source": "T37n1763_014:0436a05_0",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "僧亮曰。",
        "translation": "Sengliang said.",
        "source": "T37n1763_014:0436a05_1",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "凡聖不可相譬。",
        "translation": "\"Ordinary people and sages can't be likened to each other.",
        "source": "T37n1763_014:0436a05_2",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "若分取可借凡以明聖也。",
        "translation": "If we take them separately, we can use the worldling to illustrate the sage.",
        "source": "T37n1763_014:0436a05_3",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "雖不具足者。",
        "translation": "Even though it's not complete.",
        "source": "T37n1763_014:0436a06_4",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "逆罪有二種。",
        "translation": "There are two kinds of heinous crimes.",
        "source": "T37n1763_014:0436a06_5",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "一者但以心重。",
        "translation": "One is simply because his mind is heavy.",
        "source": "T37n1763_014:0436a06_6",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "為不具足。",
        "translation": "It's not complete.",
        "source": "T37n1763_014:0436a07_7",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "二者以心重事重。",
        "translation": "The second is because his mind is heavy with tasks.",
        "source": "T37n1763_014:0436a07_8",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "為具足。",
        "translation": "It's complete.",
        "source": "T37n1763_014:0436a07_9",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "迦葉菩薩白佛言世尊(至)當作如是護持正法。",
        "translation": "Kāśyapa said to the Buddha, \"Bhagavān, suppose you thus safeguard the right teaching.",
        "source": "T37n1763_014:0436a08_0",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "案。",
        "translation": "Commentary.",
        "source": "T37n1763_014:0436a09_0",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "智秀曰。",
        "translation": "Zhixiu said.",
        "source": "T37n1763_014:0436a09_1",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "迦葉領旨。",
        "translation": "\"Kāśyapa has received his teaching.",
        "source": "T37n1763_014:0436a09_2",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "佛讚述也。",
        "translation": "The Buddha also praised its exposition.",
        "source": "T37n1763_014:0436a09_3",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "大般涅槃經集解卷第十四",
        "translation": "Mahāparinirvāṇa-sūtra, Collected and Explained, Volume 14",
        "source": "T37n1763_014:0436a10_0",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    }
]